HEADWORD: Softa
<hw>Sof"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Corruption of Per.
<ets>s⟦omac⟧khtah</ets> one who burns, is ardent or zealous.]</ety>
<def>Any one attached to a Mohammedan mosque, esp. a student of the
higher branches of theology in a mosque school.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>sophta</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

